HEADWORD: Circum-
<hw>Cir"cum-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Akin to <ets>circle</ets>,
<ets>circus</ets>.]</ety> <def>A Latin preposition, used as a prefix in
many English words, and signifying <xex>around</xex> or
<xex>about</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Circumagitate</ent>⟦br⟧
